Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section U CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

uaclasses No caption.
This package provides a LaTeX2e document class named `ua-thesis' for typesetting theses and dissertations in the official format required by the University of Arizona. Moreover, there is a fully compatible alternative document class `my-thesis' for private ``nice'' copies of the dissertation, and the respective title pages are available as separate packages to work with ``any'' document class.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
ucthesis No caption.
A modified version of the standard LaTeX report style that is accepted for use with University of California PhD dissertations and Masters theses.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
ukhyph Hyphenation patterns for British English.
This replaces the earlier version of 1992, by adding a short list of hyphenation exceptions. The actual patterns themselves are unchanged.
license: unknown version: 2.0 (1996/10/21)
ulem Package for underlining.
Be advised that underlining is considered bad style in typesetting. See also underlin
license: dfsg (1996/05/28)
ulsy Extra mathematical characters.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
umlaute No caption.
An interface to inputenc for using alternate input encodings.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
umrand Package for page frames.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
uncial Fonts based on the Uncial manuscript book-hand used between the 3rd and 6th century AD.
The uncial and alluncl packages provide Metafont fonts based on the Uncial manuscript book-hand used between the 3rd and 6th century AD. The font consists of minuscules and digits, with some appropriate period punctuation marks. Both normal and bold versions are provided. This is one in a series of manuscript fonts.
license: lppl (1999/05/18)
underlin Package for underlining.
Be advised that underlining is considered bad style in typesetting. See also ulem which is a specific package for LaTeX.
license: unknown (1997/05/13)
underscore Make ``_'' print as \textunderscore in text.
Make ``_'' print as \textunderscore in text.
license: unknown (1998/07/17)
uni The Universal font.
An implementation of the universal font by Herbert Bayer of the Bauhaus school for MetaFont. It is supported in LaTeX with a package and font definition file.
license: gpl version: 1998/08/1 v2.0 (1999/03/26)
uniqleaf No caption.
Check filesystem tree (or union of several trees) for unique leaf names; useful for spotting ambiguities that path-searching programs could trip over. For each non-unique leaf name found, it prints out ``ls'' and ``md5'' information for each candidate file.
license: pd (1999/03/03)
units No caption.
Includes two packages for typesetting fractions and physical units.
license: dfsg (1998/08/6)
universa No caption.
An implemnatation of Herbert Bayers `universal' font, with LaTeX support.
license: unknown (1998/09/6)
unsupported MetaFont sources from Knuth, unsupported.
license: unknown (1999/03/26)
url Verbatim with URL-sensitive line breaks.
A form of \verb that allows linebreaks at certain characters or combinations of characters, accepts reconfiguration, and can usually be used in the argument to another command. It is intended for email addresses, hypertext links, directories/paths, etc., which normally have no spaces.
license: lppl version: 1.4 (1999/04/2)
urw No caption.
Font metrics, and macro support in LaTeX2e, for free URW fonts.
license: unknown (1996/05/16)
urwstd No description available.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
urwvf No caption.
A collection of virtual fonts generated with fontinst 1.6, that provide the fonts which URW has made available under the GNU License: Antiqua, Grotesk, Nimbus and Nimbus Sans, (and which are available as raw fonts urw ) in OT1, T1, 8r and OT4 encodings, to be used with LaTeX2e.
license: unknown (1998/02/5)
ut-backref No caption.
A version of bachref which adds to bibliography entries an entry saying where this particular reference was cited.
license: unknown (1998/11/10)

A LaTeX2e thesis class definition for University of Toronto.
